  "description": [
    "H fMSK BethesctaChevy Chase Montgomery Blair Springbrook o Walter Johnson o Northwood o Wheaton Exchange Student Describes 6Dav Japanese School Week By Pat Bangs There is a saying in Japan Those who sleep more than five hours will not enter college those who sleep less than four and a half might So says Masara Danbara an American Field Service exchange sutdent from Nagano Japan now enrolled at BethesdaChevy Chase High School Five hours of study nightly is not unusual for college prepar atory students in his homeland Masara revealed adding that his study period regularly extends from 7 pm until midnight Masara would have been a senior at Nagona High School a college preparatory school of J3OO students Had he remained Jn Nagano Massarus schedule would have differed from an American students and so he was asked what his school life was like in Papan Rising at 8 am Masaru usu ally ate a quick breakfast of Taw eggs seasoned in soy sauce A short 20minute walk and he arrived at school At 840 am school began with a 10minute homeroom period On TTiursdays this homeroom period was extended for inter class competition in judo bad minton volleyball and fencing"
